I managed to solve the task using the following techniques:

 1. separate the prices for tickers using `Collectors.groupingBy`. this produces a map where key is ticker and value is list of all related prices. this allows separate processing of each ticker.

		private void priceReducer(List&lt;Price&gt; prices, int intervalInSecond) {
			System.out.println(&quot;-- original list --------------&quot;);
			prices.forEach(System.out::println);
	
			List&lt;Price&gt; reducedList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

			// separate prices by ticker
			Map&lt;String, List&lt;Price&gt;&gt; pricesByTicker = prices.stream()
				.collect(Collectors.groupingBy(price -&gt; price.getTicker()));

			// process each ticker&#39;s prices separately
			pricesByTicker.values().stream()
				.map(tickerPrices -&gt; reduceForTicker(tickerPrices, intervalInSecond))
				.forEach(reducedTickerPrices -&gt; reducedList.addAll(reducedTickerPrices));
	
			System.out.println(&quot;-- reduced list ---------------&quot;);
			reducedList.forEach(System.out::println);
		}
 2. for each ticker: sort the prices by trade date, assign first entry to reduced list, then iteratively remove items from list that are within interval range of last entry of reduced, add first remaining item from prices to reduced, repeat. 

		private List&lt;Price&gt; reduceForTicker(List&lt;Price&gt; tickerPrices, int intervalInSecond) {
			List&lt;Price&gt; reducedList = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
			// sort by trade date asc
			tickerPrices.sort(Comparator.comparing(Price::getTradeDate));
			// first item added unconditionally
			reducedList.add(tickerPrices.get(0));

			while (!tickerPrices.isEmpty()) {
				// last item in reducedList signifies current minute
				Price current = reducedList.get(reducedList.size()-1);
				LocalDateTime minuteAfterCurrent = current.getTradeDate().plusSeconds(intervalInSecond);
				// relying on ordered prices, remove all prices within minute after current
				tickerPrices.removeIf(price -&gt; price.getTradeDate().isBefore(minuteAfterCurrent));
				// first item in whatever is left in prices signifies next minute
				if (!tickerPrices.isEmpty()) {
					reducedList.add(tickerPrices.get(0));
				}
			}
			return reducedList;
		}

